regnancies excluding miscarriages) <\/p>\n\n<p>Uterine prolapse makes subsequent pregnancies high-risk and can lead to fetal and maternal problems. <\/p>\n\n<p>The general risk of anything happening increases due to going through multiple pregnancies in a short time span, though. Without sufficient recovery between pregnancies, women are at a higher risk of <a href=\"http://www.mayoclinic.org/healthy-lifestyle/getting-pregnant/in-depth/family-planning/art-20044072\" rel=\"nofollow\">placental abruptions and placenta previa<\/a>. For the baby, this leads to a higher risk of premature birth with the associated issues of low birth weight and small size. <\/p>\n","answer_id":41710,"question_id":2884,"up_vote_count":1}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/2884/what-are-possible-health-risks-to-women-having-large-numbers-of-children","last_activity_date":1450870840,"creation_date":1342116008,"answer_count":2,"title":"What are possible health risks to women having large numbers of children?","body":"<p>What is the possible health issue the women would face in this record?<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>The record for most children born to a single couple belongs to the\n  first wife of Feodor Vassilyev of Russia. In 27 pregnancies between\n  1725 and 1765 she gave birth to 16 pairs of twins, 7 sets of triplets,\n  and 4 sets of quadruplets for a grand total of 69 children.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n","question_id":2884,"tags":["human-biology","reproduction"],"score":6,"accepted_answer_id":2890,"down_vote_count":1,"is_answered":true,"view_count":116,"up_vote_count":7,"last_edit_date":1342283263},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/34938175e59ce669b36ec1a35a46ecef?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6786,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6786/ooker","reputation":253,"display_name":"Ooker","accept_rate":100},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d1c6641d5c8556d9f351765c89b510f6?