 evolution and other bio-topics, but it will be a while before I can fix my code and get everything running again."}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/39389/what-are-the-branches-of-system-ecology","last_activity_date":1450864987,"creation_date":1444312829,"answer_count":0,"title":"What are the branches of system ecology?","body":"<p>What are the branches of <strong>system ecology<\/strong> that scientists research in nowadays? Or what can system ecology can applied to, or be used?<\/p>\n\n<p>I have read its <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systems_ecology\" rel=\"nofollow\">Wikipedia<\/a> page, but sadly it doesn't answer my question (or do I have an ignorance?). The most relevant section of it is the \"Closely related fields\", but again, it doesn't answer my question directly.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>For what I understand<\/strong>, system ecology is a sub-field of theoretical ecology. It uses thermodynamic in physics to explain a biological system, with the help of network thinking and some technique of visualization. I have presented this in detail <a href=\"http://lyminhnhat.com/2015/09/21/why-i-choose-ecology-to-study-in-grad-school/\" rel=\"nofollow\">what I understand<\/a> on my website.<\/p>\n","question_id":39389,"tags":["ecology","ecosystem"],"score":5,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":214,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1450864987},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6e22ae4c7de5955c6d5dea88e32069c7?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6316,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6316/isarandi","reputation":140,"display_name":"isarandi"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":0,"post_id":27992,"edited":false,"creation_date":1422115628,"comment_id":4