-based and neurophysiological knowledge.  <\/p>\n","question_id":41615,"tags":["neuroscience","brain","neurophysiology","reference-request","synapses"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"too broad","is_answered":false,"view_count":27,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1450475053},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/58c978b3f58b839f81c7424726aed509?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19989,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19989/luke","reputation":16,"display_name":"Luke"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-WkfTZcfOt8E/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACY/CiSg2Y_BtRY/photo.jpg?sz=128","user_type":"registered","user_id":19894,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19894/sanbi-samples","reputation":317,"display_name":"SANBI samples"},"score":0,"post_id":40576,"edited":false,"creation_date":1447440114,"comment_id":68341,"body":"Right on, me too, this an amazing technique that i would like to know more about."}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4897ecd6ff83143f48eebc4d33754652?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":19994,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/19994/frankyg","reputation":406,"display_name":"FrankyG"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b10de963b115fd0720d6a558fd1ac06c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10456,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10456/march-ho","reputation":5867,"display_name":"March Ho","accept_rate":80},"score":0,"post_id":40763,"edited":false,"creation_date":1450483142,"comment_id":70725,"body":"This is a link-only answer, which are <a href=\"http://meta.stackexchange.com/questions/8231/are-answers-that-just-contain-links-elsewhere-really-good-answers\">discouraged on StackExchange<\/a>. Could you describe what is in these links and include relevant areas of the te