"score":0,"post_id":38902,"edited":false,"creation_date":1442632345,"comment_id":64858,"body":"The clamps are like the enzyme. They provide a more efficient path to catalyze the reaction. Just as the clamps make each of your strokes with the saw more efficient than the exact same stroke when the wood was free to move on the slippery surface."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":1,"post_id":38902,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16651,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16651/amr","reputation":4081,"display_name":"AMR"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1442634920,"comment_id":64861,"body":"Nice description @AMR :) As an add-on - enzymes with multiple substrates often bind these substrates and bring them close to each other such that it is a near-perfect 3D confirmation to establish the bonding / breakage of chemical bonds."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":0,"post_id":38902,"edited":false,"creation_date":1442635140,"comment_id":64864,"body":"I voted to close because &quot;<i>an enzyme<\/i>&quot; is too broad. There are many enzymes that may catalyze reactions in various ways."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fcf9d3bdac2c3fa35177730c31b34f79?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":6307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6307/canadianer","reputation":6147,"display_name":"canadianer"},"score":0,"post_id":38902,"edited":false,"creation_date":1442635754,"comment_id":64866,"body":"I don&#39;t think