med as part of the BBC's 'Legends of the Deep: Deep Sea Sharks'.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/ZXnvE.jpg\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/ZXnvE.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n","question_id":39214,"tags":["species-identification","ichthyology","identification"],"score":5,"accepted_answer_id":41621,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":121,"up_vote_count":5},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96e1ceb9166745244b864fa1945a48eb?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":20700,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/20700/john","reputation":16,"display_name":"John"},"closed_date":1455182273,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16651,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16651/amr","reputation":4081,"display_name":"AMR"},"score":0,"post_id":41618,"edited":false,"creation_date":1450483288,"comment_id":70726,"body":"Are you sure they didn&#39;t mean labeled primers. The Oligonucleotides become part of your DNA, so if they are labeled, then the label will be incorporated into your amplified sample."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96e1ceb9166745244b864fa1945a48eb?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":20700,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/20700/john","reputation":16,"display_name":"John"},"score":0,"post_id":41618,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16651,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16651/amr","reputation":4081,"display_name":"AMR"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1450495957,"comment_id":70731,"body":"they described them as forward and reverse primers with overhang regions"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/INPrd.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":16651,"link":"http://biology.stackex